cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GR, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with computational geometry and algorithms for maintaining and optimizing the Oβ-hull of a planar point set, which is a fundamental concept in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves data structures and optimization techniques, which are relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The study of area and perimeter optimization falls under cs.GR (Graphics) and the fitting of a point set with a two-joint chain relates to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
